<h2 id="generalized-linear-mixed-model">Generalized Linear Mixed Model</h2>

<p>mixed: fixed effect + random effect, the old variables is called fixed effect, and they take into account the effect of different subjects</p>

<p>For example:</p>

<p><code>weight ~ height + age + gender + (height + age | subject)</code></p>

<p>fixed: height, age, gender</p>

<table>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>random: (height + age</td>
      <td>subject), this will add three weightings: 1. base subject (dummy variable coding) 2. subject on height (a vector, containing each individualâ€™s difference from mean height) 3. subject on age (same as 2)</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

